Hey, Eun Cho Rong!

146
00:15:22,110 --> 00:15:23,950
Hey, Oppa.

147
00:15:23,950 --> 00:15:26,190
You look like you're in a good mood.

148
00:15:26,190 --> 00:15:28,570
I'm not really in a good mood.

149
00:15:28,570 --> 00:15:30,570
Why not?

150
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:35,940
Because Hyun Oh says he'll never marry.

151
00:15:38,590 --> 00:15:40,890
Why are you pretending like you didn't know?

152
00:15:40,890 --> 00:15:45,260
Well, Hyung doesn't talk to me about that stuff. Want coffee?

153
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:48,650
No thanks. I have some.

154
00:15:48,650 --> 00:15:50,800
One iced Americano, please.

155
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,730
But you know...

156
00:15:53,730 --> 00:15:56,890
the grandmas are pushing for you.

157
00:15:56,890 --> 00:15:58,910
Of course.

158
00:15:58,910 --> 00:16:01,940
Who would be a better daughter-in-law than me?

159
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:06,370
But Shin Yeong seems to be against it.

160
00:16:06,370 --> 00:16:11,540
Right. She thinks marriage should be between people who like each other.

161
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:15,830
I agree with that part.

162
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:17,420
Thank you.

163
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:24,520
But Oppa.

164
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:26,350
Actually...

165
00:16:27,350 --> 00:16:28,810
I like Hyun Oh.

166
00:16:28,810 --> 00:16:30,420
What?

167
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:33,620
I thought you didn't.

168
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:36,900
You said you like our family. You said you have no interest in him.

169
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:39,700
Of course, I like your family.

170
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:42,260
But I also like him.

171
00:16:42,260 --> 00:16:45,570
If I told him that, I thought he'd be even more against it.

172
00:16:45,570 --> 00:16:48,730
Hey, if Hyun Oh knows that...

173
00:16:57,590 --> 00:16:59,070
Wow.

174
00:17:02,330 --> 00:17:04,150
Eun Cho Rong.

175
00:17:04,150 --> 00:17:06,840
Can you explain it slowly again?

176
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:12,990
- Well...
- You don't like me.

177
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:15,030
But you like my family.

178
00:17:15,030 --> 00:17:18,970
You said that's why you wanted to marry me.

179
00:17:18,970 --> 00:17:21,600
I can't say I didn't consider it.

180
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:24,610
- What? Really?
- Don't get too excited.

181
00:17:25,450 --> 00:17:29,300
Because now that I know you like me,

182
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:32,150
I feel a lot more pressure.

183
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,560
That makes sense.

184
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:41,520
Yes. As you know, I don't like you at all.

185
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:46,300
But Sunbae...

186
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,700
I do like you, but...

187
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:52,680
I won't insist that you like me back.

188
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:55,200
I just love your family so much.

189
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:58,940
Liking someone who doesn't like you might hurt you.

190
00:17:58,940 --> 00:18:02,760
No. I'm strong about this kind of stuff.

191
00:18:06,510 --> 00:18:09,100
Then, let me be more clear.

192
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:14,670
I don't want to be the bad guy who hurts someone.

193
00:18:16,330 --> 00:18:19,540
But Sunbae, I can't give up yet...

194
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:23,080
Eun Cho Rong, please respect someone else's feelings, too.

195
00:18:23,830 --> 00:18:27,880
Until now, I considered it a little bit.

196
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:29,970
But not anymore.

197
00:18:29,970 --> 00:18:34,290
Eun Cho Rong, we will never get married.

198
00:18:38,110 --> 00:18:42,520
So, please don't bring up marriage again anywhere.

199
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:49,680
Okay, Sunbae.

200
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,180
I'll do that.

201
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:54,870
Then, let's get back to work.

202
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:03,910
But Sunbae...

203
00:19:04,860 --> 00:19:10,160
you're so gentle even after saying such cruel things.

204
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:15,470
I don't need to be cold to you.

205
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:20,070
Where are you headed? The office?

206
00:19:20,070 --> 00:19:22,800
Yes. I'm going to the office.

207
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:26,310
By the way, Grandma Mi Ja wants us to gather later.

208
00:19:26,310 --> 00:19:28,060
What do you think she wants to say?

209
00:19:28,060 --> 00:19:30,290
Not sure. I don't know.

210
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:37,730
They say there's some improvement.

211
00:19:37,730 --> 00:19:39,870
Unbelievable.

212
00:19:39,870 --> 00:19:41,900
That's unbelievable.

213
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:46,090
What is? Me getting better?

214
00:19:46,090 --> 00:19:48,430
You've been rubbing me the wrong way this whole time.

215
00:19:48,430 --> 00:19:51,990
Do you want me to die? Or-

216
00:19:51,990 --> 00:19:55,860
Unni! She's crying tears of joy.

217
00:19:55,860 --> 00:19:58,270
Don't go too far.

218
00:19:58,270 --> 00:20:04,280
Then, I can relax now and have a smoke.

219
00:20:05,190 --> 00:20:07,460
No smoking.

220
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:10,830
But she's allowed to drink! Why not me?

221
00:20:10,830 --> 00:20:14,670
Grandma Young Ja has a very clean liver.

222
00:20:14,670 --> 00:20:17,240
But what did the doctor say to you?

223
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:21,280
That I should stop smoking.

224
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,640
Yes, that's right.

225
00:20:24,510 --> 00:20:26,980
Aigoo, after you got cancer,

226
00:20:26,980 --> 00:20:30,270
Hyun Oh's nagging got worse.

227
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:33,610
Hyun Oh, don't worry.

228
00:20:33,610 --> 00:20:36,050
I'm a lot better, so-

229
00:20:36,050 --> 00:20:38,370
How does cancer get better?

230
00:20:38,370 --> 00:20:40,640
You need to keep getting treatment.

231
00:20:42,780 --> 00:20:45,640
Hey. If I just stay-

232
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:48,340
Unni! Unni!

233
00:20:48,340 --> 00:20:49,900
Grandma!

234
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:52,150
What do I do?

235
00:20:52,150 --> 00:20:53,770
What?

236
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:01,220
Noona...

237
00:21:03,020 --> 00:21:05,330
Shin Yeong...

238
00:21:06,290 --> 00:21:09,020
Hurry. Hurry up and leave!

239
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:12,190
And don't call me again. Got it?

240
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:15,170
Hey, Shin Yeong, this is-

241
00:21:16,670 --> 00:21:18,390
Damn it.

242
00:21:30,550 --> 00:21:32,140
Eat up.

243
00:21:32,140 --> 00:21:36,770
Do Hyeong, where were you, and what have you been up to?

244
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,120
I've been everywhere.

245
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:44,340
Mountains, boats...

246
00:21:44,340 --> 00:21:47,770
You two are so cringe. Stop holding hands.

247
00:21:47,770 --> 00:21:51,740
No way. I haven't held this hand in forever.

248
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:54,170
Aigoo, so nice and warm.

249
00:21:56,320 --> 00:22:00,290
She used to be cute. What happened to her?

250
00:22:00,290 --> 00:22:01,780
I don't know.

251
00:22:01,780 --> 00:22:06,830
I don't know when it happened, either. It's a real mystery.

252
00:22:07,890 --> 00:22:10,680
- Honey, want more rice?
- Yes.

253
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:13,400
We should raise a glass on a day like this.

254
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:17,750
We have an expensive bottle that Hyun Oh brought back from a business trip!

255
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:19,610
- Grandma, no.
- Why not?

256
00:22:19,610 --> 00:22:22,460
- I'm healthy!
- No.

257
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:25,400
Why is he so straight-edge now?

258
00:22:26,310 --> 00:22:30,520
Do Hyeong, ever since Mi Ja got cancer,

259
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:33,150
he's lost his mind.

260
00:22:33,150 --> 00:22:36,680
- Completely.
- No.

261
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:40,700
I think it happened after he didn't get the 9 o'clock anchor job.

262
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:46,270
No. I think it happened after Eun Ho disappeared.

263
00:22:46,270 --> 00:22:48,050
Stop it.

264
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:53,390
Give it to me. Hyung, I'll do it.

265
00:22:53,390 --> 00:22:55,110
You can't do that?

